    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. It's just frustrating because when the noise is that high, it's like the data is behaving totally unpredictably. Is there a concept for when the noise is so erratic that it makes the signal almost impossible to track, or is that just what we call high variance/low precision?",
